"n.铁匠铺；v.锤炼；伪造 【英】 n. 铁匠铺(smithy)；v. 锤炼(to form or shape)；伪造(counte rfeit) 【考】 pirate : take / forge : copy(掠夺是非法拿/伪造 是非法复制)mill : grain / forge : metal(磨房用来磨谷物/铁 匠铺用来锻造金属)反义词: lag(落后)-forge ahead(稳步前进)forge[fO:dZ]v. (迎着困难)稳步前进 ； 【英】 v. (迎着困难)稳步前进( to move forward) 【例】 to forge ahead with one's plans n. (将生铁锻造成熟铁的)铁匠铺; v 锻制(将金属在锻炉上高温加热并锤打成形); 伪造(为欺骗的目的而复制) = counterfeit; 突然加速前进 【参】forger(n 伪造者; 铁匠) 【类】pirate: take = forge: copy 掠夺是非法拿 = 伪造是非法复制mill: grain = forge: metal 磨房磨谷物 = 铁匠铺锻造金属 【反】lag(vi 缓缓而行; 滞后)－forge ahead(v 突然加速前进) 【记】音：复制(该词主要是制的意思)→伪造，制造，铸造，锻造，(锻压机)稳步向前,铁匠铺里仿造 forge (n.)  late 14c., ""a smithy,"" from Old French forge (12c.) ""forge, smithy,"" earlier faverge, from Latin fabrica ""workshop,"" from faber (genitive fabri) ""workman in hard materials, smith"" (see fabric). As the heating apparatus itself, from late 15c. forge (v.2)  1610s, ""make way, move ahead,"" of unknown origin, perhaps an alteration of force (v.), but perhaps rather from forge (n.), via notion of steady hammering at something. Originally nautical, in reference to vessels. forge (v.1)  c.1300, ""to make, shape, create,"" from Old French forgier, from Latin fabricari ""to frame, construct, build,"" from fabrica ""workshop"" (see forge (n.)). Meaning ""to counterfeit"" is early 14c. Related: Forged; forging."
